To implement the merge sort algorithm in Java, we can use a recursive approach. The merge sort algorithm divides the array into two halves, recursively sorts each half, and then merges the two sorted halves. To achieve the specified complexity requirements, we will modify the given array in-place without using any additional data structures.

Here's the Java code to implement the merge sort algorithm:

```java
public class MergeSort {

    public static void mergeSort(int[] array) {
        if (array == null || array.length <= 1) {
            return;
        }
        mergeSort(array, 0, array.length - 1);
    }

    private static void mergeSort(int[] array, int left, int right) {
        if (left < right) {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            mergeSort(array, left, mid);
            mergeSort(array, mid + 1, right);
            merge(array, left, mid, right);
        }
    }

    private static void merge(int[] array, int left, int mid, int right) {
        int[] temp = new int[right - left + 1];
        int i = left;
        int j = mid + 1;
        int k = 0;
        while (i <= mid && j <= right) {
            if (array[i] >= array[j]) {
                temp[k++] = array[i++];
            } else {
                temp[k++] = array[j++];
            }
        }
        while (i <= mid) {
            temp[k++] = array[i++];
        }
        while (j <= right) {
            temp[k++] = array[j++];
        }
        for (int m = 0; m < temp.length; m++) {
            array[left + m] = temp[m];
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] array = {5, 3, 9, 1, 8, 2};
        mergeSort(array);
        for (int num : array) {
            System.out.print(num + " ");
        }
    }
}
```

This code defines a `MergeSort` class with a `mergeSort` method that takes an integer array as input and sorts it in descending order using the merge sort algorithm. It also includes a `merge` method to merge the two sorted halves during the merging step of the merge sort algorithm.

In the `main` method, an example array is created and sorted using the `mergeSort` method. The sorted array is then printed to the console.

To use this code, you can copy it into a Java file, compile the file, and run the program. The output will be the sorted array in descending order: 9 8 5 3 2 1.

